name: app/Data/graph-utils.js

params.name: width
params.description: Width to create the scale with.

params.name: minY
params.description: Minimum y value to use in our domain.

params.name: maxY
params.description: Maximum y value to use in our domain.

name: createLineGraph
description:
Creates a line graph SVG path that we can then use to render in our
React Native application with ART.

params.name: options.data
params.description:
Array of data we'll use to create
  our graphs from.

params.name: xAccessor
params.description: Function to access the x value from our data.

params.name: yAccessor
params.description: Function to access the y value from our data.

params.name: width
params.description: Width our graph will render to.

params.name: height
params.description: Height our graph will render to.

return.description: Object with data needed to render.
